      • authorizationCode

        public AuthorizationCodeRequest.Builder authorizationCode​(String client_id,
                                                          String client_secret,
                                                          String code,
                                                          String redirect_uri)
        Returns a builder that can be used to build requests for authorization code grants. Requires client ID, client secret, and redirect URI to be set.
        Parameters:
        client_id - Required. When you register your application, Spotify provides you a Client ID.
        client_secret - Required. When you register your application, Spotify provides you a Client Secret.
        code - Required. The authorization code returned from the initial request to the Account /authorize endpoint.
        redirect_uri - Required. This parameter is used for validation only (there is no actual redirection). The value of this parameter must exactly match the value of redirect_uri supplied when requesting the authorization code.
        Returns:
        A builder that builds authorization code grant requests.

        public AuthorizationCodeUriRequest.Builder createAuthorizeUri​(String client_id,
                                                              String redirect_uri)
        Retrieve a URL where the user can give the application permissions.
        Parameters:
        client_id - Required. When you register your application, Spotify provides you a Client ID.
        redirect_uri - Required. This parameter is used for validation only (there is no actual redirection). The value of this parameter must exactly match the value of redirect_uri supplied when requesting the authorization code.
        Returns:
        The URL where the user can give application permissions.
